Starting with the equation: 5500 = 1500 · e^(0.23t)  Divide both sides by 1500: 5500/1500 = e^(0.23t) 3.666... = e^(0.23t)  Take the natural logarithm of both sides: ln(3.666...) = ln(e^(0.23t)) ln(3.666...) = 0.23t  Solve for t: t = ln(3.666...)/0.23  Calculate ln(11/3): ln(11/3) ≈ 1.2993  Therefore: t = 1.2993/0.23 ≈ 5.649</answer1>  <answer2>5.64923975496262934408845906218834459930313588850174</answer2>
